Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 124 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 138, 1 Name Teisamenos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0217.38.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1149)
